# Local Worker Health ([PROJECT_NAME])

Read when: configuring, validating, or troubleshooting the local worker lane.
Skip when: the project is cloud-only or local-worker delegation is disabled.

Purpose: prove the local worker is healthy before issuing implementation packets. This generalizes the ASUS endpoint-smoke lesson without assuming a specific machine, model, or VS Code extension.

## Current Worker Route

- Local worker enabled: YES / NO / PLANNED
- Worker tool/client: `<CLIENT_OR_EXTENSION>`
- Endpoint type: OpenAI-compatible / native extension / local CLI / other
- Endpoint URL or command: `<PRIVATE_OR_LOCAL_ONLY_VALUE>`
- Primary coding model: `<MODEL_NAME>`
- Tool-calling support required: YES / NO
- Last health check: `<YYYY-MM-DD>`
- Health status: OK / DEGRADED / OFFLINE / UNKNOWN

Do not store secrets here. Store real tokens, private hostnames, and credentials in the operator's private config, not in repo docs.

## Minimum Health Checks

Before local-worker implementation packets are allowed:

- [ ] Worker endpoint or command is reachable from the development machine.
- [ ] Expected model is visible or selectable.
- [ ] Worker can read one allowed file and summarize it accurately.
- [ ] Worker can produce a small edit in a sandbox or doc-only packet.
- [ ] Worker can run the allowed command set or clearly report command limitations.
- [ ] Worker returns structured result packets instead of broad prose.
- [ ] Timeout behavior is known and recorded in `docs/state/session_budget.json` or active plan notes.

## Sandbox And Secret Boundary

- Worker execution location: same checkout / dedicated worktree / disposable checkout / remote sandbox
- Secrets available to worker: NO / YES + rationale
- Network access during worker loop: NONE / LAN / INTERNET + rationale
- Push/deploy allowed from worker: NO unless explicitly packet-authorized
- Tier C ready: YES / NO / N/A

For Tier C or sensitive-data work, local-worker implementation packets are blocked until secrets are unavailable by default and rollback/snapshot commands are recorded in the packet.

## Optional Endpoint Smoke Command

If the worker exposes an OpenAI-compatible endpoint, create a project-specific smoke script such as:

```bash
python3 scripts/check_openai_compatible_endpoint.py \
  --base-url http://<local-worker-host>:<port>/v1 \
  --api-key test-key \
  --expect-model <model-or-alias>
```

If no endpoint exists, replace this with the exact local CLI or extension smoke path.

## Degraded / Offline Rules

- Attended session: one bounded cloud-only fallback slice is allowed only when already in plan and surfaced to the operator.
- Unattended session: halt instead of falling back to cloud-only.
- Infrastructure outage is not investigator work.
- Two malformed or timed-out results after the worker is otherwise healthy means the worker setup needs tuning before more packets.

